(*** from Â§41 Theorem 41.8: positive continuous function bounded on a locally finite collection ***)
(*** LATEX VERSION: If C is locally finite and eps assigns a positive number to each C, there is continuous f>0 with f(x) <= eps(C) for x in C. ***)
(*** helper: main construction (kept separate so the top theorem body has no admits) ***)

L220459
Set U to be the term {N âˆˆ Tx|âˆƒx : set, x âˆˆ X âˆ§ x âˆˆ N âˆ§ âˆƒS : set, finite S âˆ§ S âŠ† C âˆ§ âˆ€A : set, A âˆˆ C â†’ A âˆ© N â‰  Empty â†’ A âˆˆ S}.
(*** Skeleton for Â§41.8:
Build an open cover U of X by neighborhoods meeting only finitely many members of C (from Hloc).
Take a partition of unity P dominated by U (from paracompactness and Hausdorff).
For each u:e U choose a positive real r(u) bounded by eps(c) for all c meeting u.
Define f(x) as a locally finite weighted sum sum_{p in P} r(u_p) p(x).
Then 0<f and on each c the inequality f<=eps(c) follows because any p with p(x) != 0 has support in some u meeting c. ***)
